<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-14T07:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-14T07:40:00-05:00" n="306" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1715.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Johnson</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]<note n="8" xml:id="d306fn8">The entire telegram is printed under Political Affairs, <ref target="#pg_288">p. 288</ref>.</note></seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-14T08:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1915—8 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Heavy inroads on funds appropriated for other purposes have been made for
                            war operations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>